In order to collect all necessary information to display the feeding guide, weâ€™ll determine a model interface (following [DDD model standards|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/c7a7475b516a137aa12abd9e70a648610641db0c/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/libraries/services/README.md]).
This interface should establish the necessary data to populate the feeding guide with the pet and feeding information. These attributes should be defined based on the info displayed in the feeding guideâ€™s design.

Store this in the services directory under {{feeding-guide}}

!image-20251125-162346 (ae681c08-662f-4415-9da4-fa4325c30334).png|width=359,height=813,alt="image-20251125-162346.png"!
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
This is a recommended interface structure. It splits the necessary information in three groups: Pet info, Product and Feedings:

{noformat}import { Fraction } from 'fraction.js';

export interface FeedingGuide {
  pet: Pet;
  product: Product;
  feedings: Feeding[];
  transitions: Transition[];
}

export interface Pet {
  name: string;
  breed: string;
  weight: number;
  activityLevel: string;
  bodyCondition: string;
}

export interface Product {
  sku: string;
  family: string;
  selectionIndex: number;
  portionPercentage: number;
  isTrialPlan: boolean;
}

export interface Feeding {
  recipeType: 'dry' | 'fresh';
  portionShare: Fraction;
  getUnit(): 'cup' | 'packet' | undefined;
  // Get the portion share according to amount of times feeding happens per day
  getMultipleFeedingPerDay: (timesPerDay: number) => Fraction;
}

export interface Transition {
  daysRange: number[];
  percentagePetsTableFood: number;
}
{noformat}
{panel}

